                  "ElementType": 1
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "FullText": "Whenever a value is set to on a Property object, if the corresponding Property has a validator configured, the value will",
              "Elements": [
                {
                  "RawText": "Whenever a value is set to on a Property object, if the corresponding Property has a validator configured, the value will",
                  "ElementType": 1
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "FullText": "be validated, throwing a validation error, if the value is not compliant with the validation restrictions. For example,",
              "Elements": [
                {
                  "RawText": "be validated, throwing a validation error, if the value is not compliant with the validation restrictions. For example,",
                  "ElementType": 1
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "FullText": "a validator can check the written value for lower-than, greater-than, equality, or other number relations.",
              "Elements": [
